history.content:
Hi, I am a returning student who recently got readmitted and trying to enroll for upper div cs courses for Fall 22. Since 10 + days have past since opening of phase 1, almost every single upper div cs courses are already filled and have high numbers of waitlist. 

Since I have already took 170, 188, 186, the choices for me is really narrow. 

Are there chances for courses like cs 164 or cs 194(computer vision) to increase its capacity? Or how likely is it to get off waitlist of (wait list number of. 100+) for these mentioned courses? I feel like there is simply way too much of demand for upper div cs courses compared to its open seats. 

 

Edited) Plus, will it be smart to remain on the waitlist even though my waitlist number is (100/100) for cs164 on phase 1, rather than enrolling into other non-cs courses that is currently open?
history.subject: Chances of getting off waitlist
